Dear Participant,

We hope this message finds you well.

This is a friendly reminder to retake our Antimicrobial Resistance (AMR) Data Collection Survey. Your participation is crucial for understanding and combating antibiotic resistance in our community.

The survey includes questions such as:
- How are you feeling today? (e.g., Do you have any symptoms?)
- Please describe your symptoms (e.g., fever, sore throat, cough, etc.)
- Are you taking any medication today?
- Please upload a photo of your current medication packaging.
- Where did you obtain your medicine? (e.g., hospital, clinic, pharmacy, friend, at home, etc.)
- Did you have a prescription for the medicine?
- How many days have you been taking the medicine?
- Do you think your medicine contains antibiotics?
- Optionally, you can upload photos of any other medications you are taking.

Your feedback on the survey itself, such as your overall experience, how long it took to complete, and suggestions for improvement, is also highly valuable.

